	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Oct 14th 3:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When soloing, feedback is one of the 3 spells i have memmed for my pet.... along with zerk strength and sltw.&nbsp;&nbsp;Now, if you don't solo, and you're often in the company of a druid, ranger, or mage... and they have the mana to burn on your pet, it's not real useful.  If you find yourself soloing anything blue at level 52, and you don't use feedback, you're asking to die.<br><br>If you use your chanter only to pl your alts, go play your alts.  If you think the spell is useless, you haven't tested the bounds of what you can do as a chanter.  You may go out and quiver and grovel for help to kill that IG, i already know i can take one.<br><br>Don't get me wrong, everyone has their own playstyle; but, when people say a spell is useless, it makes me think they've never bothered to find out how to use it.  Feedback is one of the turning point spells in a chanters life.  <br><br>If you don't understand, go solo 3 seafuries in a row without medding (with you in the area of level 50).  Try it useing Feedback, then try it without feedback.  When you try it without feedback, be sure to save enough mana on the second one to gate out.<br><br>As for the earring, it's nice.  Better than a batskull at this level, assuming your over your 187 intel.  It's recast time seems to be about what the regular spell is, and it can be cast on anyone you can target, given they're within range.<br>&nbsp;<br>Moraganth<br><br>Good brewer, better drunk</td></tr>
