<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=1002734908378></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1002734908378><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6802&mid=1002734908378>Feedback's Usefullness</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6802&mid=1002734908378#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=68492><span id= >necrro</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 10th 1:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Played a ENC on MT till 53.&nbsp;&nbsp;While there was no shortage of needy groups, I did solo quite a bit more than most ENCs I know.  Let me tell you that Feedback was an absolute must and I used it every time.  First, you do not need an extra spell slot.  It is just like any other "buff".  You cast it on your pet just before pulling the mob.  Thus, you cast it, sit down, mem appropriate spell, get up and get into the fight.  While it may not be the best damage shield in the game or even close, it does help and can make the difference.  I have often reviewed the mesage logs after a fight while medding.  Let me tell you that most fights result in more than 10 hits to my pet per fight even when the mob is slowed.  Thus, with feedback doing as much as 12 per hit thats over 120 hps, its like having a nuke.  120 is 120 no matter how you cut it.  It helps, even if it simply offsets the mobs regen rate.  Bottom line, I used it alot as a chanter.  Just my preference.  Everyone has their own style.  No one style is best, the only thing that matters is you survive the fight, get exp and reload for the next round.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
